The Portuguese government plans to
limit the salaries earned by managers at state-owned companies,
Diario Economico reported, without saying how it obtained the
information.  Managers of state-owned companies will not be allowed to
earn more than the prime minister, or about 5,300 euros a month,
the Portuguese newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  